Probably shouldn&#x27;t be &quot;hard&quot; coding the scheme (http). Check $_SERVER[&#x27;https&#x27;]. You can make sure this fastcgi param exists with a simple directive in nginx (fastcgi_params):<p><pre><code>    fastcgi_param  HTTPS  $https if_not_empty;
</code></pre>
Also, the 404 route, should be able to be defined as a custom function:<p><pre><code>    Macaw::fourofour(function() {
        header($_SERVER[&quot;SERVER_PROTOCOL&quot;] . &quot; 404 Not Found&quot;);
        header(&quot;Status: 404 Not Found&quot;);
    });</code></pre>
